Trump distances himself from escalating tensions, declaring “It’s not my war” as he slams Putin for going “absolutely crazy” amid intensifying strikes on Ukraine. The Kremlin fires back, calling Trump “emotional,” while reports emerge that Putin’s helicopter was nearly taken out in a failed drone assassination attempt—an attack Trump claims he knew nothing about. With Putin now threatening to put the West in a “chokehold” and blaming elites for staging a “bloody coup” in Ukraine, are we entering the most dangerous phase yet?
